      <title>Use the default Compose Bridge transformation</title>
      <link>https://docker.qubitpi.org/compose/bridge/usage/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://docker.qubitpi.org/compose/bridge/usage/</guid>
      <description>&lt;div class=&#34;px-4 border-l-2 border-l-magenta-light dark:border-l-magenta-dark&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;p class=&#34;not-prose flex gap-2 items-center text-magenta-light dark:text-magenta-dark&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;span class=&#34;icon-svg pb-1&#34;&gt;&#xA;      &lt;svg xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#34; width=&#34;48&#34; height=&#34;48&#34; viewBox=&#34;0 -960 960 960&#34;&gt;&lt;path d=&#34;M172-120q-41.78 0-59.39-39T124-230l248-280v-270h-52q-12.75 0-21.37-8.68-8.63-8.67-8.63-21.5 0-12.82 8.63-21.32 8.62-8.5 21.37-8.5h320q12.75 0 21.38 8.68 8.62 8.67 8.62 21.5 0 12.82-8.62 21.32-8.63 8.5-21.38 8.5h-52v270l248 280q29 32 11.39 71T788-120H172Z&#34;/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/span&gt;&#xA;    &lt;strong&gt;Experimental&lt;/strong&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Compose Bridge is an &#xA;    &#xA;    &#xA;  &#xA;  &lt;a class=&#34;link&#34; href=&#34;https://docker.qubitpi.org/release-lifecycle/#experimental&#34;&gt;Experimental&lt;/a&gt; product.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Compose Bridge supplies an out-of-the box transformation for your Compose configuration file. Based on an arbitrary &lt;code&gt;compose.yaml&lt;/code&gt; file, Compose Bridge produces:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;A &#xA;  &lt;a&#xA;    class=&#34;link&#34;&#xA;    href=&#34;https://kubernetes.io/docs/concepts/overview/working-with-objects/namespaces/&#34;&#xA;    rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;Namespace&lt;span class=&#34;pl-1 icon-svg icon-sm&#34;&gt;&lt;svg xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#34; width=&#34;48&#34; height=&#34;48&#34; viewBox=&#34;0 -960 960 960&#34;&gt;&lt;path d=&#34;M180-120q-24 0-42-18t-18-42v-600q0-24 18-42t42-18h249q12.75 0 21.38 8.68 8.62 8.67 8.62 21.5 0 12.82-8.62 21.32-8.63 8.5-21.38 8.5H180v600h600v-249q0-12.75 8.68-21.38 8.67-8.62 21.5-8.62 12.82 0 21.32 8.62 8.5 8.63 8.5 21.38v249q0 24-18 42t-42 18H180Zm600-617L403-360q-9 9-21 8.5t-21-9.5q-9-9-9-21t9-21l377-377H549q-12.75 0-21.37-8.68-8.63-8.67-8.63-21.5 0-12.82 8.63-21.32 8.62-8.5 21.37-8.5h261q12.75 0 21.38 8.62Q840-822.75 840-810v261q0 12.75-8.68 21.37-8.67 8.63-21.5 8.63-12.82 0-21.32-8.63-8.5-8.62-8.5-21.37v-188Z&#34;/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; so all your resources are isolated and don&#39;t conflict with resources from other deployments.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;A &#xA;  &lt;a&#xA;    class=&#34;link&#34;&#xA;    href=&#34;https://kubernetes.io/docs/concepts/configuration/configmap/&#34;&#xA;    rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;ConfigMap&lt;span class=&#34;pl-1 icon-svg icon-sm&#34;&gt;&lt;svg xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#34; width=&#34;48&#34; height=&#34;48&#34; viewBox=&#34;0 -960 960 960&#34;&gt;&lt;path d=&#34;M180-120q-24 0-42-18t-18-42v-600q0-24 18-42t42-18h249q12.75 0 21.38 8.68 8.62 8.67 8.62 21.5 0 12.82-8.62 21.32-8.63 8.5-21.38 8.5H180v600h600v-249q0-12.75 8.68-21.38 8.67-8.62 21.5-8.62 12.82 0 21.32 8.62 8.5 8.63 8.5 21.38v249q0 24-18 42t-42 18H180Zm600-617L403-360q-9 9-21 8.5t-21-9.5q-9-9-9-21t9-21l377-377H549q-12.75 0-21.37-8.68-8.63-8.67-8.63-21.5 0-12.82 8.63-21.32 8.62-8.5 21.37-8.5h261q12.75 0 21.38 8.62Q840-822.75 840-810v261q0 12.75-8.68 21.37-8.67 8.63-21.5 8.63-12.82 0-21.32-8.63-8.5-8.62-8.5-21.37v-188Z&#34;/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; with an entry for each and every &#xA;    &#xA;    &#xA;  &#xA;  &lt;a class=&#34;link&#34; href=&#34;https://docker.qubitpi.org/reference/compose-file/configs/&#34;&gt;config&lt;/a&gt; resource in your Compose application.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&#xA;  &lt;a&#xA;    class=&#34;link&#34;&#xA;    href=&#34;https://kubernetes.io/docs/concepts/workloads/controllers/deployment/&#34;&#xA;    rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;Deployments&lt;span class=&#34;pl-1 icon-svg icon-sm&#34;&gt;&lt;svg xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#34; width=&#34;48&#34; height=&#34;48&#34; viewBox=&#34;0 -960 960 960&#34;&gt;&lt;path d=&#34;M180-120q-24 0-42-18t-18-42v-600q0-24 18-42t42-18h249q12.75 0 21.38 8.68 8.62 8.67 8.62 21.5 0 12.82-8.62 21.32-8.63 8.5-21.38 8.5H180v600h600v-249q0-12.75 8.68-21.38 8.67-8.62 21.5-8.62 12.82 0 21.32 8.62 8.5 8.63 8.5 21.38v249q0 24-18 42t-42 18H180Zm600-617L403-360q-9 9-21 8.5t-21-9.5q-9-9-9-21t9-21l377-377H549q-12.75 0-21.37-8.68-8.63-8.67-8.63-21.5 0-12.82 8.63-21.32 8.62-8.5 21.37-8.5h261q12.75 0 21.38 8.62Q840-822.75 840-810v261q0 12.75-8.68 21.37-8.67 8.63-21.5 8.63-12.82 0-21.32-8.63-8.5-8.62-8.5-21.37v-188Z&#34;/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; for application services. This ensures that the specified number of instances of your application are maintained in the Kubernetes cluster.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&#xA;  &lt;a&#xA;    class=&#34;link&#34;&#xA;    href=&#34;https://kubernetes.io/docs/concepts/services-networking/service/&#34;&#xA;    rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;Services&lt;span class=&#34;pl-1 icon-svg icon-sm&#34;&gt;&lt;svg xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#34; width=&#34;48&#34; height=&#34;48&#34; viewBox=&#34;0 -960 960 960&#34;&gt;&lt;path d=&#34;M180-120q-24 0-42-18t-18-42v-600q0-24 18-42t42-18h249q12.75 0 21.38 8.68 8.62 8.67 8.62 21.5 0 12.82-8.62 21.32-8.63 8.5-21.38 8.5H180v600h600v-249q0-12.75 8.68-21.38 8.67-8.62 21.5-8.62 12.82 0 21.32 8.62 8.5 8.63 8.5 21.38v249q0 24-18 42t-42 18H180Zm600-617L403-360q-9 9-21 8.5t-21-9.5q-9-9-9-21t9-21l377-377H549q-12.75 0-21.37-8.68-8.63-8.67-8.63-21.5 0-12.82 8.63-21.32 8.62-8.5 21.37-8.5h261q12.75 0 21.38 8.62Q840-822.75 840-810v261q0 12.75-8.68 21.37-8.67 8.63-21.5 8.63-12.82 0-21.32-8.63-8.5-8.62-8.5-21.37v-188Z&#34;/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; for ports exposed by your services, used for service-to-service communication.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&#xA;  &lt;a&#xA;    class=&#34;link&#34;&#xA;    href=&#34;https://kubernetes.io/docs/concepts/services-networking/service/&#34;&#xA;    rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;Services&lt;span class=&#34;pl-1 icon-svg icon-sm&#34;&gt;&lt;svg xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#34; width=&#34;48&#34; height=&#34;48&#34; viewBox=&#34;0 -960 960 960&#34;&gt;&lt;path d=&#34;M180-120q-24 0-42-18t-18-42v-600q0-24 18-42t42-18h249q12.75 0 21.38 8.68 8.62 8.67 8.62 21.5 0 12.82-8.62 21.32-8.63 8.5-21.38 8.5H180v600h600v-249q0-12.75 8.68-21.38 8.67-8.62 21.5-8.62 12.82 0 21.32 8.62 8.5 8.63 8.5 21.38v249q0 24-18 42t-42 18H180Zm600-617L403-360q-9 9-21 8.5t-21-9.5q-9-9-9-21t9-21l377-377H549q-12.75 0-21.37-8.68-8.63-8.67-8.63-21.5 0-12.82 8.63-21.32 8.62-8.5 21.37-8.5h261q12.75 0 21.38 8.62Q840-822.75 840-810v261q0 12.75-8.68 21.37-8.67 8.63-21.5 8.63-12.82 0-21.32-8.63-8.5-8.62-8.5-21.37v-188Z&#34;/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; for ports published by your services, with type &lt;code&gt;LoadBalancer&lt;/code&gt; so that Docker Desktop will also expose the same port on the host.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&#xA;  &lt;a&#xA;    class=&#34;link&#34;&#xA;    href=&#34;https://kubernetes.io/docs/concepts/services-networking/network-policies/&#34;&#xA;    rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;Network policies&lt;span class=&#34;pl-1 icon-svg icon-sm&#34;&gt;&lt;svg xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#34; width=&#34;48&#34; height=&#34;48&#34; viewBox=&#34;0 -960 960 960&#34;&gt;&lt;path d=&#34;M180-120q-24 0-42-18t-18-42v-600q0-24 18-42t42-18h249q12.75 0 21.38 8.68 8.62 8.67 8.62 21.5 0 12.82-8.62 21.32-8.63 8.5-21.38 8.5H180v600h600v-249q0-12.75 8.68-21.38 8.67-8.62 21.5-8.62 12.82 0 21.32 8.62 8.5 8.63 8.5 21.38v249q0 24-18 42t-42 18H180Zm600-617L403-360q-9 9-21 8.5t-21-9.5q-9-9-9-21t9-21l377-377H549q-12.75 0-21.37-8.68-8.63-8.67-8.63-21.5 0-12.82 8.63-21.32 8.62-8.5 21.37-8.5h261q12.75 0 21.38 8.62Q840-822.75 840-810v261q0 12.75-8.68 21.37-8.67 8.63-21.5 8.63-12.82 0-21.32-8.63-8.5-8.62-8.5-21.37v-188Z&#34;/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; to replicate the networking topology defined in your &lt;code&gt;compose.yaml&lt;/code&gt; file.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&#xA;  &lt;a&#xA;    class=&#34;link&#34;&#xA;    href=&#34;https://kubernetes.io/docs/concepts/storage/persistent-volumes/&#34;&#xA;    rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;PersistentVolumeClaims&lt;span class=&#34;pl-1 icon-svg icon-sm&#34;&gt;&lt;svg xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#34; width=&#34;48&#34; height=&#34;48&#34; viewBox=&#34;0 -960 960 960&#34;&gt;&lt;path d=&#34;M180-120q-24 0-42-18t-18-42v-600q0-24 18-42t42-18h249q12.75 0 21.38 8.68 8.62 8.67 8.62 21.5 0 12.82-8.62 21.32-8.63 8.5-21.38 8.5H180v600h600v-249q0-12.75 8.68-21.38 8.67-8.62 21.5-8.62 12.82 0 21.32 8.62 8.5 8.63 8.5 21.38v249q0 24-18 42t-42 18H180Zm600-617L403-360q-9 9-21 8.5t-21-9.5q-9-9-9-21t9-21l377-377H549q-12.75 0-21.37-8.68-8.63-8.67-8.63-21.5 0-12.82 8.63-21.32 8.62-8.5 21.37-8.5h261q12.75 0 21.38 8.62Q840-822.75 840-810v261q0 12.75-8.68 21.37-8.67 8.63-21.5 8.63-12.82 0-21.32-8.63-8.5-8.62-8.5-21.37v-188Z&#34;/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; for your volumes, using &lt;code&gt;hostpath&lt;/code&gt; storage class so that Docker Desktop manages volume creation.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&#xA;  &lt;a&#xA;    class=&#34;link&#34;&#xA;    href=&#34;https://kubernetes.io/docs/concepts/configuration/secret/&#34;&#xA;    rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;Secrets&lt;span class=&#34;pl-1 icon-svg icon-sm&#34;&gt;&lt;svg xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#34; width=&#34;48&#34; height=&#34;48&#34; viewBox=&#34;0 -960 960 960&#34;&gt;&lt;path d=&#34;M180-120q-24 0-42-18t-18-42v-600q0-24 18-42t42-18h249q12.75 0 21.38 8.68 8.62 8.67 8.62 21.5 0 12.82-8.62 21.32-8.63 8.5-21.38 8.5H180v600h600v-249q0-12.75 8.68-21.38 8.67-8.62 21.5-8.62 12.82 0 21.32 8.62 8.5 8.63 8.5 21.38v249q0 24-18 42t-42 18H180Zm600-617L403-360q-9 9-21 8.5t-21-9.5q-9-9-9-21t9-21l377-377H549q-12.75 0-21.37-8.68-8.63-8.67-8.63-21.5 0-12.82 8.63-21.32 8.62-8.5 21.37-8.5h261q12.75 0 21.38 8.62Q840-822.75 840-810v261q0 12.75-8.68 21.37-8.67 8.63-21.5 8.63-12.82 0-21.32-8.63-8.5-8.62-8.5-21.37v-188Z&#34;/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; with your secret encoded. This is designed for local use in a testing environment.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;It also supplies a Kustomize overlay dedicated to Docker Desktop with:&lt;/p&gt;</description>
