    <item>
      <title>Customize Compose Bridge</title>
      <link>https://docker.qubitpi.org/compose/bridge/customize/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://docker.qubitpi.org/compose/bridge/customize/</guid>
      <description>&lt;div class=&#34;px-4 border-l-2 border-l-magenta-light dark:border-l-magenta-dark&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;p class=&#34;not-prose flex gap-2 items-center text-magenta-light dark:text-magenta-dark&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;span class=&#34;icon-svg pb-1&#34;&gt;&#xA;      &lt;svg xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#34; width=&#34;48&#34; height=&#34;48&#34; viewBox=&#34;0 -960 960 960&#34;&gt;&lt;path d=&#34;M172-120q-41.78 0-59.39-39T124-230l248-280v-270h-52q-12.75 0-21.37-8.68-8.63-8.67-8.63-21.5 0-12.82 8.63-21.32 8.62-8.5 21.37-8.5h320q12.75 0 21.38 8.68 8.62 8.67 8.62 21.5 0 12.82-8.62 21.32-8.63 8.5-21.38 8.5h-52v270l248 280q29 32 11.39 71T788-120H172Z&#34;/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/span&gt;&#xA;    &lt;strong&gt;Experimental&lt;/strong&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Compose Bridge is an &#xA;    &#xA;    &#xA;  &#xA;  &lt;a class=&#34;link&#34; href=&#34;https://docker.qubitpi.org/release-lifecycle/#experimental&#34;&gt;Experimental&lt;/a&gt; product.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;This page explains how Compose Bridge utilizes templating to efficiently translate Docker Compose files into Kubernetes manifests. It also explain how you can customize these templates for your specific requirements and needs, or how you can build your own transformation.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Advanced integration</title>
      <link>https://docker.qubitpi.org/compose/bridge/advanced-integration/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://docker.qubitpi.org/compose/bridge/advanced-integration/</guid>
      <description>&lt;div class=&#34;px-4 border-l-2 border-l-magenta-light dark:border-l-magenta-dark&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;p class=&#34;not-prose flex gap-2 items-center text-magenta-light dark:text-magenta-dark&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;span class=&#34;icon-svg pb-1&#34;&gt;&#xA;      &lt;svg xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#34; width=&#34;48&#34; height=&#34;48&#34; viewBox=&#34;0 -960 960 960&#34;&gt;&lt;path d=&#34;M172-120q-41.78 0-59.39-39T124-230l248-280v-270h-52q-12.75 0-21.37-8.68-8.63-8.67-8.63-21.5 0-12.82 8.63-21.32 8.62-8.5 21.37-8.5h320q12.75 0 21.38 8.68 8.62 8.67 8.62 21.5 0 12.82-8.62 21.32-8.63 8.5-21.38 8.5h-52v270l248 280q29 32 11.39 71T788-120H172Z&#34;/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/span&gt;&#xA;    &lt;strong&gt;Experimental&lt;/strong&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Compose Bridge is an &#xA;    &#xA;    &#xA;  &#xA;  &lt;a class=&#34;link&#34; href=&#34;https://docker.qubitpi.org/release-lifecycle/#experimental&#34;&gt;Experimental&lt;/a&gt; product.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Compose Bridge can also function as a &lt;code&gt;kubectl&lt;/code&gt; plugin, allowing you to integrate its capabilities directly into your Kubernetes command-line operations. This integration simplifies the process of converting and deploying applications from Docker Compose to Kubernetes.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
